-- Qatar's Ooredoo signs Islamic loans worth $498 mln -statement
-- By Matt Smith
-- Tue May 13, 2014 01:26PM EDT
-- None



DUBAI, May 13 (Reuters) - Qatar's Ooredoo <ORDS.QA> has signed three Islamic loan facilities with local banks totalling $498 million, the telecommunications operator said on Tuesday.

Ooredoo, which has operations in Africa, Asia and the Middle East, has agreed one-year murabahas - a sharia-compliant cost-plus-profit arrangement - of $166 million each with Qatar Islamic Bank <QISB.QA>, Masraf Al-Rayyan <MARK.QA> and Barwa Bank.